Euler's method: $S_{n+1}=S_{n}+h \cdot \frac{d S}{d t}, h=0.2, \frac{d S}{d t}=0.1 S\left(1-\frac{S}{200}\right)$. At $t_{0}=0$, $S_{0}=10$ :

$$
\begin{gathered}
\frac{d S}{d t}=0.1 \cdot 10 \cdot\left(1-\frac{10}{200}\right)=0.95 \\
S_{1}=10+0.2 \cdot 0.95=10.19
\end{gathered}
$$

At $t_{1}=0.2, S_{1}=10.19$ :

$$
\begin{gathered}
\frac{d S}{d t} \approx 0.954 \\
S_{2} \approx 10.3808 \mathrm{~m}^{2}
\end{gathered}
$$

[3 marks]

Euler's method: $A_{n+1}=A_{n}+h \cdot \frac{d A}{d t}, h=0.5, \frac{d A}{d t}=-0.08 A+4$. At $t_{0}=0, A_{0}=100$ :

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{d A}{d t}=-0.08 \cdot 100+4=-4 \\
& A_{1}=100+0.5 \cdot(-4)=98
\end{aligned}
$$

At $t_{1}=0.5, A_{1}=98$ :

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{d A}{d t}=-0.08 \cdot 98+4=-3.84 \quad(M 1) \\
A_{2}= & 98+0.5 \cdot(-3.84)=96.08 \text { becquerels }
\end{aligned}
$$

[3 marks]

Differentiate $x^{2}+y^{2}=e^{x y}$:

$$
\begin{array}{r}
2 x+2 y \frac{d y}{d x}=e^{x y}\left(y+x \frac{d y}{d x}\right) \\
2 x+2 y \frac{d y}{d x}=y e^{x y}+x e^{x y} \frac{d y}{d x} \\
2 y \frac{d y}{d x}-x e^{x y} \frac{d y}{d x}=y e^{x y}-2 x \\
\frac{d y}{d x}=\frac{y e^{x y}-2 x}{2 y - x e^{x y}}
\end{array}
$$

